<ns3028:section xmlns:ns3028="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="knowledge.concepts.architecture.mda.tools.tools">
    
    <ns3029:title xmlns:ns3029="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">MDA supporting tools</ns3029:title>
  <ns3030:para xmlns:ns3030="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    There is an ever increasing number of MDA supporting tools available. Here we provide a
    non-exhaustive list of some of these.
  </ns3030:para>

  <ns3031:section xmlns:ns3031="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3032:title xmlns:ns3032="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">AndroMDA</ns3032:title>
    <ns3033:para xmlns:ns3033="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      AndroMDA is an open-source MDA tool which generates different concrete Java-based realizations
      from an XMI-based platform independent model using maven and ant plugins. The XMI model would
      be generated by some UML tool.
    </ns3033:para>
    <ns3034:para xmlns:ns3034="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      AndroMDA provides a
      collection of cartridges which map architectural elementsPIM model elements onto technology realizations. For
      example, AndroMDA provides cartridges for 
      <ns3035:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3035="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns3036:listitem xmlns:ns3036="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3037:para xmlns:ns3037="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">EJB,</ns3037:para></ns3036:listitem>
        <ns3038:listitem xmlns:ns3038="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3039:para xmlns:ns3039="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Struts,</ns3039:para></ns3038:listitem>
        <ns3040:listitem xmlns:ns3040="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3041:para xmlns:ns3041="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Sping framework,</ns3041:para></ns3040:listitem>
        <ns3042:listitem xmlns:ns3042="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3043:para xmlns:ns3043="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Apache Axis based web services, and</ns3043:para></ns3042:listitem>
        <ns3044:listitem xmlns:ns3044="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3045:para xmlns:ns3045="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">hibernate based persistence layer.</ns3045:para></ns3044:listitem>
      </ns3035:itemizedlist>
      AndroMDA uses the design specified in a PIM and a set of cartridges chosen from an architecture specification
      to generate directly an EDM. 
    </ns3034:para>
    <ns3046:para xmlns:ns3046="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      For example, one can specify an architecture to use
      <ns3047:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3047="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns3048:listitem xmlns:ns3048="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3049:para xmlns:ns3049="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">a Struts based presentation layer,</ns3049:para></ns3048:listitem>
        <ns3050:listitem xmlns:ns3050="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3051:para xmlns:ns3051="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBoss-EJB based business logic layer, and</ns3051:para></ns3050:listitem>
        <ns3052:listitem xmlns:ns3052="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3053:para xmlns:ns3053="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">and Apache-Axis based webs services front-end</ns3053:para></ns3052:listitem>
      </ns3047:itemizedlist>
      and AndroMDA will generate from that architecture specification and a PIM an EDM containing
      the code for the various layers.
    </ns3046:para>
  </ns3031:section>
  
  <ns3054:section xmlns:ns3054="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3055:title xmlns:ns3055="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">OpenMDX</ns3055:title>
    <ns3056:para xmlns:ns3056="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      OpenMDX is an open-source MDA tool which supports the generation of J2SE, J2EE, Java/CORBA and
      .Net based PSMs from a MOF-Complient UML based PIM.
    </ns3056:para>
  </ns3054:section>
  
  
  <ns3057:section xmlns:ns3057="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3058:title xmlns:ns3058="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Codagen Architect</ns3058:title>
    <ns3059:para xmlns:ns3059="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Codagen architect is a commercial MDA tool which can be plugged into UML tools like Rational Rose. One
      can specify the mapping of PIM elements onto architectural elements. It supports the
      generation of JavaEE and .Net based systems from a PIM.
    </ns3059:para>
  </ns3057:section>
  
  <ns3060:section xmlns:ns3060="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3061:title xmlns:ns3061="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Mia Software</ns3061:title>
    <ns3062:para xmlns:ns3062="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Mia software provides MIA Transformation which can be used to transform a PIM onto a PSM and
      MIA Generation which can be used to tranform a PSM onto an EDM. It supports a range of
      architectural mappings including JavaEE and .Net.
    </ns3062:para>
  </ns3060:section>
  
  <ns3063:section xmlns:ns3063="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3064:title xmlns:ns3064="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">OptimalJ</ns3064:title>
    <ns3065:para xmlns:ns3065="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      OptimalJ is a commercial Java-centric UML tool supporting MDA. It can map PIMs onto JavaEE
      based EDMs.
    </ns3065:para>
  </ns3063:section>
  
  
</ns3028:section>